{
  "info": {
    "name": "PullApp",
    "_postman_id": "pullapp-collection-v1",
    "description": "All HTTP endpoints for PullApp services.\n\nVariables:\n- `base_url`         — gateway (default: http://localhost:8080, via `make pf-gateway`)\n- `accounts_url`     — accounts direct (default: http://localhost:5001)\n- `trip_planner_url` — trip-planner direct (default: http://localhost:5002)\n- `token`            — JWT; set automatically by the Login request test script\n- `userId`           — set automatically by the Login request test script\n- `routeId`          — paste from CreateRoute response\n- `requestId`        — paste from CreateRideRequest response\n- `rideId`           — paste from AcceptRideRequest response\n\nAuth flow via gateway:\n  1. POST /api/auth/register → register user\n  2. POST /api/auth/login    → captures `token` + `userId`\n  3. All trip-planner requests via gateway use Bearer token; gateway injects X-User-Id.\n\nDirect service access (trip-planner folder):\n  Uses `X-User-Id` header directly — useful when bypassing gateway.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",            "value": "http://localhost:8080", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "accounts_url",        "value": "http://localhost:5001", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "trip_planner_url",    "value": "http://localhost:5002", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "notifications_url",   "value": "http://localhost:5003", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_tracker_url",  "value": "http://localhost:5004", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token",               "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "userId",              "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "routeId",             "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "requestId",           "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "rideId",              "value": "",                      "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Accounts",
      "description": "Auth endpoints exposed at /api/auth/* (anonymous, no JWT required).\nAll requests go through the gateway which forwards them to the accounts service.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "register"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Jan\",\n  \"surname\": \"Kowalski\",\n  \"email\": \"jan.kowalski@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Secret123!\",\n  \"birthDate\": \"1995-06-15\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Registers a new user.\n\n201 Created → { userId }\n409 Conflict → email already taken"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.accessToken);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"jan.kowalski@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Secret123!\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Logs in and returns a JWT.\n\n200 OK → { accessToken }\n401 Unauthorized → bad credentials\n\nTest script captures `token` collection variable automatically."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Trip Planner — via Gateway",
      "description": "Trip-planner endpoints reached through the gateway.\nAll requests require a valid JWT (`Authorization: Bearer {{token}}`).\nThe gateway validates the JWT and injects X-User-Id / X-User-Role headers before forwarding.\n\nGateway route: /api/route/{**catch-all} → trip-planner service",
      "auth": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
      },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Driver",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Create Route",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/driver/routes",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "driver", "routes"]
                },
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"start\": { \"latitude\": 52.2297, \"longitude\": 21.0122 },\n  \"end\":   { \"latitude\": 52.2500, \"longitude\": 21.0400 },\n  \"capacity\": 3\n}",
                  "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
                },
                "description": "Driver submits a new route. Geometry is computed asynchronously by route-calc.\n\n202 Accepted → { routeId }\n403 Forbidden → driver not authorised to drive\n422 Unprocessable → start/end outside service area\n503 Service Unavail → accounts or route-calc unavailable"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Activate Route",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/driver/routes/{{routeId}}/activate",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "driver", "routes", "{{routeId}}", "activate"]
                },
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"currentLocation\": { \"latitude\": 52.2297, \"longitude\": 21.0122 }\n}",
                  "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
                },
                "description": "Driver signals they are at the start location and ready.\nWaitingForActivation rides transition to WaitingForDriver.\n\n204 No Content\n403 Forbidden → route belongs to different driver\n404 Not Found\n409 Conflict → route not in Created status\n422 Unprocessable → driver not near Route.Start"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Delete Route",
              "request": {
                "method": "DELETE",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/driver/routes/{{routeId}}",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "driver", "routes", "{{routeId}}"]
                },
                "description": "Driver deletes a route. Passengers with accepted rides are notified.\n\n204 No Content\n403 Forbidden → route belongs to different driver\n404 Not Found\n409 Conflict → route is Active and has existing rides"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Accept Ride Request",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/driver/requests/{{requestId}}/accept",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "driver", "requests", "{{requestId}}", "accept"]
                },
                "description": "Driver accepts a pending RideRequest. Creates a Ride; may mark route Full.\nIf route became Full, remaining pending requests are auto-rejected.\n\n200 OK → { rideId, chatRoomId }\n403 Forbidden → request belongs to different driver's route\n404 Not Found → ride request not found\n409 Conflict → route is Full, or request is no longer Pending\n503 Service Unavail → payments or chat unavailable"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Reject Ride Request",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/driver/requests/{{requestId}}/reject",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "driver", "requests", "{{requestId}}", "reject"]
                },
                "description": "Driver rejects a pending RideRequest. Passenger funds are unfrozen.\n\n204 No Content\n403 Forbidden → request belongs to different driver's route\n404 Not Found → ride request not found\n409 Conflict → request is no longer Pending\n503 Service Unavail → payments unavailable"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Declare Driver Pickup",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/driver/rides/{{rideId}}/pickup",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "driver", "rides", "{{rideId}}", "pickup"]
                },
                "description": "Driver declares the passenger has been picked up.\nRide transitions to Started only after passenger also declares pickup.\n\n204 No Content\n403 Forbidden → ride belongs to different driver\n404 Not Found\n409 Conflict → ride not in WaitingForDriver status"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Declare Driver End",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/driver/rides/{{rideId}}/end",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "driver", "rides", "{{rideId}}", "end"]
                },
                "description": "Driver declares the ride is over.\nPassenger must declare end first; out-of-order returns 403.\nWhen both declare: payment charged, events published.\n\n204 No Content\n403 Forbidden → ride belongs to different driver, or passenger hasn't declared end yet\n404 Not Found\n409 Conflict → ride not in Started status\n503 Service Unavail → payments unavailable"
              },
              "response": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Passenger",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Submit Route Search",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/passenger/routes/search",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "passenger", "routes", "search"]
                },
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"start\": { \"latitude\": 52.2297, \"longitude\": 21.0122 },\n  \"end\":   { \"latitude\": 52.2500, \"longitude\": 21.0400 }\n}",
                  "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
                },
                "description": "Passenger submits a route search. Matching is async via RabbitMQ/route-calc.\nResults delivered via SSE/push (RouteSearchCompletedEvent).\n\n202 Accepted → { jobId }\n422 Unprocessable → start/end outside service area\n503 Service Unavail → route-calc unavailable"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Create Ride Request",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/passenger/routes/{{routeId}}/requests",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "passenger", "routes", "{{routeId}}", "requests"]
                },
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"start\": { \"latitude\": 52.2300, \"longitude\": 21.0130 },\n  \"end\":   { \"latitude\": 52.2480, \"longitude\": 21.0380 }\n}",
                  "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
                },
                "description": "Passenger picks a route and creates a RideRequest.\nPrice quoted and funds frozen atomically via payments service.\nDriver notified via RideRequestedEvent.\n\n201 Created → { requestId }\n404 Not Found → route not found\n409 Conflict → route is Full\n422 Unprocessable → passenger start/end outside service area\n503 Service Unavail → payments unavailable"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Cancel Ride",
              "request": {
                "method": "DELETE",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/passenger/rides/{{rideId}}",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "passenger", "rides", "{{rideId}}"]
                },
                "description": "Passenger cancels a ride before it starts.\n  WaitingForActivation → no charge, funds unfrozen.\n  WaitingForDriver     → cancellation fee charged, remainder unfrozen.\n  Started              → 409 (use POST .../end instead).\n\n204 No Content\n403 Forbidden → ride belongs to different passenger\n404 Not Found\n409 Conflict → ride is Started\n503 Service Unavail → payments unavailable"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Declare Passenger Pickup",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/passenger/rides/{{rideId}}/pickup",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "passenger", "rides", "{{rideId}}", "pickup"]
                },
                "description": "Passenger confirms they have been picked up.\nDriver must declare pickup first; out-of-order returns 403.\nRide transitions to Started when both parties have declared.\n\n204 No Content\n403 Forbidden → ride belongs to different passenger, or driver hasn't declared yet\n404 Not Found\n409 Conflict → ride not in WaitingForDriver status"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Declare Passenger End",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/route/passenger/rides/{{rideId}}/end",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "route", "passenger", "rides", "{{rideId}}", "end"]
                },
                "description": "Passenger declares the ride is over. Must declare BEFORE the driver.\nFull completion (payment + events) happens when driver also calls their /end.\n\n204 No Content\n403 Forbidden → ride belongs to different passenger\n404 Not Found\n409 Conflict → ride not in Started status"
              },
              "response": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
